h2 Resize text
div.chi-grid
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .chi-breadcrumb
      ol.-text--normal
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank") WCAG 2.0 Guideline
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/#visual-audio-contrast" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank") 1.4 Distinguishable
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/#visual-audio-contrast-scale" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank") 1.4.4 Resize text
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .-lh--3
      .chi-badge.-dark.-outline.-xs(data-tooltip="Content must be presentable to users in ways they can perceive." data-position="bottom")
        span Perceivable
      .chi-badge.-dark.-outline.-xs.-ml--1(data-tooltip="Requirements must be satisfied to pass WCAG 2.0 Level AA Success Criteria." data-position="bottom")
        span Level AA
  .chi-col.-w--12
    p.-text
      | <strong>Benefits:</strong> Low vision disabilities.
    p.-text
      | Except for captions and images of text, text can be resized without Assistive Technology up to 200 percent without loss of content or functionality.
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .chi-card.-s--1.-rounded.-mb--3.-mt--1
      .chi-card__header
        .chi-card__title
          | How to pass
      .chi-card__content.-px--3
        ul.accessibility-checklist
          li 
            | Can visually rendered text be scaled successfully so that it can be read directly by people with mild visual disabilities, without requiring the use of Assistive Technologies such as a screen magnifier?
          li 
            | Including text-based controls (text characters that have been displayed so that they can be seen vs. text characters that are still in data form such as ASCII).
          li 
            | Can content be scaled up to 200% - up to twice the width and height?

